                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Aug. 5: Insurance regulator IRDA has issued the final guidelines on corporate governance for the sector focusing on areas such as control functions, board of directors, governance structure and disclosures. On disclosure requirements, the IRDA guidelines said that insurers should provide quantitative and qualitative information on their financial and operating ratios such as incurred claim, commission and expenses ratios.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 5: Foreign companies cannot be discriminated vis-a-vis Indian firms in taxation of capital gains from securities transactions, according to an order by the Authority for Advance Rulings.                             
	 Calcutta, Aug. 5: National Aluminium Co expects aluminium prices to reach $2,000 a tonne by December on rising demand. Aluminium prices fell more than half to a low of around $1,300 a tonne as the recession cut into demand from the auto and construction sectors.                                                                                                                           
